Package org.microbean.type

Class Type.Semantics

java.lang.Object
org.microbean.type.Type.Semantics
Direct Known Subclasses:
Type.VariantSemantics
Enclosing class:
Type<T>
@Experimental public abstract static class Type.Semantics extends Object
An abstract embodiment of Type assignability rules.

By default, no Type is assignable to any other Type except itself. Subclasses will obviously want to override this behavior in some, if not all, cases.

Author:
Laird Nelson

  • Method Details

    • assignable

      @Convenience public boolean assignable(Type receiverType, Type payloadType)
      Returns true if and only if a reference bearing the type modeled by the supplied payloadType is assignable to a reference bearing the type modeled by the supplied receiverType, according to the assignability rules modeled by this Type.Semantics instance, and using no autoboxing.

      This is a convenience method that creates JavaTypes to represent the supplied Types before calling the (canonical) assignable(Type, Type) method.

      Parameters:
      receiverType - the receiver type as described above; must not be null
      payloadType - the payload type as described above; must not be null
      Returns:
      true if and only if a reference bearing the type modeled by the supplied payloadType is assignable to a reference bearing the type modeled by the supplied receiverType, according to the assignability rules modeled by this Type.Semantics instance, and using no autoboxing; false otherwise
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if either receiverType or payloadType is null
      See Also:
      • assignable(Type, Type)
      • JavaType.of(java.lang.reflect.Type, boolean)
      Idempotency:
      This method is, and its overrides must be, idempotent and deterministic.
      Thread Safety:
      This method is, and its overrides must be, safe for concurrent use by multiple threads.
